Tour de France champion Chris Froome said that he had his bike written off by an impatient driver in a hit-and-run incident. LONDON - Tour de France champion Chris Froome said on Tuesday that he had his bike written off by an impatient driver in a hit-and-run incident.The 31-year-old three-time winner of the world s biggest bike race, who has been training in the south of France, tweeted a picture of the twisted remains of his totalled training bike, saying he had been deliberately knocked off by the driver.Froome said he was okay after the incident, while also posting an emoji of hands clasped in prayer.Just got rammed on purpose by an impatient driver who followed me onto the pavement! Thankfully I'm okay Bike totaled. Driver kept going! pic.twitter.com/o7FT4iXsAo Just got rammed on purpose by an impatient driver who followed me onto the pavement! Thankfully I m okay. Bike totalled. Driver kept going! the Team Sky rider wrote.